![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/1621432489794-C9FFB8OC1F8F31L724JL/178.jpg)

Five years ago, arguably the greatest entry in Marvel's Cinematic Universe, Captain America: Civil War, made its debut in theaters around the world. Not only did it introduce us to the MCU Spider-Man and Black Panther but the film itself was a masterclass in building on the tension from past films. Half a decade later does the film still hold up? What are the effects the Disney+ shows have on films like this? Is the Winter Soldier water activated? We'll be talking all this and more in this retro review of Captain America: Civil War!

Please leave us a **_review_** on [**ITunes**](https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/major-issues-podcast/id1321720972) so we can grow our audience and grow as podcasters! Rate us where ever podcasts are found. Don't forget to check out our [merchandise](http://www.teepublic.com/user/comicbookclique)! All episodes of Major Issues are brought to you by [**ComicBookClique.com**](../episode/update/id/Comicbokclique.com), the home for the latest and greatest things to come to comic books and comic book media.  
  
